org.eng.aisp.feature.io

Class AbstractFeatureWriter

  • java.lang.Object
    • org.eng.aisp.feature.io.AbstractFeatureWriter
  • Direct Known Subclasses:
    CSVFeatureWriter

    public abstract class AbstractFeatureWriter
extends Object
    Provides most of the work needed to extract and then write features extracted from a set of IDataWindows. Subclasses must implement #write(Writer, int, int, ILabeledFeature).
    Author:
    dawood

      • write

        public abstract void write(Writer writer,
                           int windowIndex,
                           int subwindowIndex,
                           IFeature<double[]> feature,
                           Properties labels)
                    throws IOException
        Write out the given labeled feature.
        Parameters:
        writer -
        windowIndex - 0-based index of window given to write(Writer, Iterable) from which the feature was extracted.
        subwindowIndex - 0-based index of the sub-window within a data window from which the given feature was extracted.
        feature - feature extracted from the Nth sub-window of the Mth data window.
        labels - labels for those features.
        Throws:
        IOException
